Patch Set 4:

I think you misunderstood, the code would look like this:

int cdt_llog_process(const struct lu_env *env, struct mdt_device *mdt,
		     llog_cb_t cb, void *data, int rw)
{
	return cdt_llog_process_range(env, mdt, cb, data, 0, 0, rw);
}

There are many places in the patch which call cdt_llog_process with the 0, 0 argument, but only one which actually utilizes the values.
